YELLOW FEVER - SOUTH AMERICA: UPDATE (02)
**********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 7 Aug 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[There are 2 international sources for current cases of YF in the Americas:
WHO Geneva & PAHO (Pan American Health Organization).
WHO: As of 6 Aug 2003, the latest YF report from WHO was posted 13 Jul
2003, showing data up to 2 Jul reported to WHO during the week 4-10 Jul
2003 -- see ref. at end. On 9 Jul 2003, within that same reporting period,
PAHO reported an additional 3 cases (1 death) for Brazil, and an additional
12 cases (7 deaths) for Colombia -- see [1] below.
PAHO: has 2 pages on its website for YF statistics for 2003 -- see below. -
Mod.JW]
******
[1]
Date: 7 Aug 203
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: PAHO Division of Vaccines and Immunization (HVP) 9 Jul 2003
(uploaded to web 14 Jul 2003) [edited]
<http://www.paho.org/English/AD/FCH/IM/2003_07_%2009_dc.pdf>

Country: No. Cases/ No. Deaths/ Last case reported/ Date of most recent report
Bolivia: 4 / 3 / EW* 13 / EW 20 (21 Apr 2003)
Brazil: 62 / 23 EW 21 / EW 20 [should be 19] (15 Apr)[includes data
labeled EW 21]
Colombia: 27 / 17 / EW 26 / EW 27 (2 Jul 2003)
Peru: 7 / 4 deaths / EW 17 / EW 24 (23 May 2003)
Venezuela: 3 / 2 / EW 2 / EW NA (21 Mar 2003)
*EW = Epidemiological Week
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The total comes to 103 cases with 49 deaths. Note there are only 15, not
20, weeks in the year up to 21 April, and there are 3 Epidemiological Weeks
between EW 24 and 27, but 40 days (over 5 weeks) between 23 May and 2 Jul,
the dates given for those weeks (Peru & Colombia above). -- Mod.JW]
******
[2]
Date: 7 Aug 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: PAHO EID Weekly Updates on Emerging & Re-emerging Infectious
Diseases, Region of the Americas
17 Jul 2003 [edited]
<http://www.paho.org/English/AD/DPC/CD/eid-eer-17-jul-2003.htm>

Jungle Yellow Fever in the Americas
-------------------------------------
Up to Epidemiological Week EW 29 [16 Jul 2003], a total of 109 cases
of Jungle Yellow Fever (JYF), with 50 deaths, have been reported to PAHO by:
Bolivia (4)
Brazil (62)
Colombia (33)
Peru (7)
Venezuela (3)
The distribution of cases by EW is presented in a graph [see URL above].
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[These figures show 6 more cases from Colombia since the report above,
which apparently have not yet been reported to WHO. - Mod.JW]
